Process Engineer / Business Analyst - Private Markets Operations

Job Information

LGT Capital Partners is a leading alternative investment specialist with over USD 60 billion in assets under 
management and more than 550 institutional clients in 39 countries. An international team of over 500 professionals is 
responsible for managing a wide range of investment programs focusing on private markets, liquid alternatives and 
multi-asset class solutions. Headquartered in Pfaeffikon (SZ), Switzerland, the firm has offices in New York, Dublin, 
London, Paris, Frankfurt, Vaduz, Dubai, Beijing, Hong Kong, Tokyo and Sydney.

- Act as member of project teams within all Private Markets areas;
- Support & perform Private Markets process engineering and subsequently business requirements analysis;
- Help driving our effort on business process modelling, process analysis, engineering and documenting capability and 
standards;
- Facilitate process workshops to elicit process requirements;
- Liaise with process owners and participants to manage process change;
- Document processes using business process modelling notations (BPMN, CMMN, DMN);
- Responsible to drive assigned improvement, changes and efficiency gains;
- Support the interaction of business and IT.

Requirements

- University degree in information technology, business administration or equivalent;
- Experience in Private Markets; masters or post graduate in Banking & Finance is considered a plus;
- Working experience in financial services company or with a leading consulting firm, previous experience in asset 
management is a plus;
- Demonstrated ability in process engineering;
- Proven business analysis skills;
- Driven personality with eagerness to solve problems, improve processes;
- Self-motivated and ability to work independently;
- Fluency in English; German a plus;
- Excellent presentation and communication (orally and written) skills.

Contact Information

If you are interested in becoming an integral part of a successful alternative investment management team in an 
international, multicultural working environment we will be pleased to get to know you soon.

For further information please contact our HR Business Partner, Ms Franziska Rohner.

